Pavement gives out to gravel, and gravel gives out to two ruts with a crown of grass down the middle. Cottage roads. You crawl along watching for your turnoff, the lake somewhere off to your left behind a wall of cedar.

The day's heat is lifting off the rock now, the first cool breath of evening coming up out of the bush. Mosquitoes find the open window. You roll it up.

